title: Cannock: Woman bitten by suspected XL bullies
title_page: Cannock: Woman bitten by suspected XL bullies - BBC News
maintext:
A woman has been seriously injured after being bitten by two dogs in Staffordshire.
Police were called to Allport Road in Cannock shortly before 13:00 GMT on Thursday after the incident near the Citizens Advice Bureau.
One of the dogs was believed to be an XL bully and the other an XL bully cross, Staffordshire Police said.
The woman has been taken to hospital with an arm injury and the dogs have been seized while officers investigate.
